    "Model Question Types Domains Overall Conversation Description CXR MRI Histology Gross CT (Question Count) (143) (50) (37) (38) (44) (34) (40) (193) LLaVA-Med-10K 42.4 32.5 46.1 36.7 43.5 34.7 37.5 39.9 LLaVA-Med-60K 53.7 36.9 57.3 39.8 49.8 47.4 52.4 49.4frequency for type-k healthcare data holders, and R k is the reward given to type-k healthcare data holders as an incentive for its contribution.",
    "To guarantee that each healthcare data holder opts for the most advantageous contract item for its type, the designed contract must adhere to both Incentive Compatibility (IC) and Individual Rationality (IR) constraints.",
    "Definition 1.",
    "(IR)The contract item for a type-k healthcare data holder guarantees a non-negative utility, formulated asR k - f k δ k ≥ 0, ∀k ∈ K. (8)Definition 2.",
    "(IC) A healthcare data holder of type-k will choose the contract item (f k, R k) tailored to its type rather than any other contract item(f i, R i), i ∈ K, and i ̸ = k, i.e., R k - f k δ k ≥ R i - f i γ k, ∀k, i ∈ K, k ̸ = i."
